<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1230,2011]" box="[151,682,1230,1255]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,682,1230,1255]" fontSize="10" level="2" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" reason="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,682,1230,1255]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<taxonomicName box="[151,341,1230,1255]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Carcharhinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carcharhiniformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Carcharhinidae</taxonomicName>
(Whaler or requiem sharks)
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1230,2011]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
The silvertip shark 
<taxonomicName authority="Ruppell, 1837" authorityName="Ruppell" authorityYear="1837" box="[416,932,1266,1291]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Carcharhinidae" genus="Carcharhinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carcharhiniformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="albimarginatus">
<emphasis box="[416,748,1267,1291]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Carcharhinus albimarginatus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ruppell" box="[763,924,1266,1290]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refString="Ruppell, W. P. E. S. (1837) Neue Wirbelthiere zu der Fauna von Abyssinien gehorig. Fische des Rothen Meeres. Frankfurt-am- Main." type="book" year="1837">
Rüppell, 
<number box="[867,924,1266,1290]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="1837.0">1837</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
was recorded by 
<bibRefCitation author="Goubanov" box="[1131,1431,1266,1290]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refString="Goubanov, E. P. &amp; Shleib, N. A. (1980). Sharks of the Arabian Gulf. Ministry of Public Works, Agricultural Department, Fisheries Divisions, Kuwait." type="book" year="1980">
Goubanov &amp; Shleib (
<number box="[1371,1431,1266,1290]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="1980.0">1980</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; subsequently noted in 
<bibRefCitation author="Bishop" box="[401,552,1302,1326]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refString="Bishop, J. M. (2003) History and current checklist of Kuwait's ichthyofauna. Journal of Arid Environments, 54, 237 - 256." type="journal article" year="2003">
Bishop, 
<number box="[495,552,1302,1326]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="2003.0">2003</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) as seldom encountered in the southern Gulf although they did not present evidence; Randall (
<number box="[335,393,1338,1362]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="1996.0">1996</number>
) considered this record doubtful. This species is generally associated with shelf waters, offshore islands, reefs, and banks, and near drop-offs, with the nearest confirmed records from the Red Sea and the 
<collectingCountry box="[151,255,1410,1434]" name="Maldives" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Maldives</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Compagno" box="[272,535,1410,1435]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refString="Compagno, L., Dando, M., &amp; Fowler, S. (2005) A field guide to the sharks of the world. Harper Collins, London." type="book" year="2005">
Compagno 
<emphasis box="[406,458,1411,1435]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[475,535,1410,1434]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</bibRefCitation>
); it was not recorded in 
<collectingCountry box="[820,896,1410,1434]" name="Oman" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Omani</collectingCountry>
surveys (
<bibRefCitation author="Henderson" box="[1008,1269,1410,1435]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refString="Henderson, A. C., McIlwain, J. L., Al-Oufi, H. S. &amp; Al-Sheili, S. (2007) The Sultanate of Oman shark fishery: Species composition, seasonality and diversity. Fisheries Research, 86, 159 - 168." type="journal article" year="2007">
Henderson 
<emphasis box="[1141,1193,1411,1435]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[1210,1269,1410,1434]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="2007.0">2007</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Henderson" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refString="Henderson, A. C. &amp; Reeve, A. J. (2011) Noteworthy elasmobranch records from Oman. African Journal of Marine Science, 33, 171 - 175." type="journal article" year="2011">
Henderson &amp; Reeve, 
<number box="[235,294,1446,1470]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="2011.0">2011</number>
</bibRefCitation>
); it is considered unlikely to be present in the Gulf.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1230,2011]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
A single specimen of a shark morphologically similar to, but clearly distinct from, 
<taxonomicName box="[1140,1296,1483,1507]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Carcharhinidae" genus="Carcharhinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carcharhiniformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dussumieri">
<emphasis box="[1140,1296,1483,1507]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">C. dussumieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, was photographed by the lead author in 
<collectingCountry box="[495,577,1518,1542]" name="Kuwait" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Kuwait</collectingCountry>
in 
<date box="[616,740,1518,1542]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="2008-04">
April 
<number box="[684,740,1518,1542]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="2008.0">2008</number>
</date>
but not retained. Whole specimens are needed to resolve the identity of this species (W. White, 
<collectionCode box="[538,621,1554,1578]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/0k2v-y6wz" name="Australian National Fish Collection" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">CSIRO</collectionCode>
Marine Research, pers. comm.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1230,2011]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
The silky shark 
<taxonomicName authority="Muller &amp; Henle, 1839" authorityName="Muller &amp; Henle" authorityYear="1839" box="[380,940,1590,1614]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Carcharhinidae" genus="Carcharhinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carcharhiniformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="falciformis">
<emphasis box="[380,663,1590,1614]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Carcharhinus falciformis</emphasis>
(Müller &amp; Henle, 
<number box="[875,932,1590,1614]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="1839.0">1839</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
is abundant in 
<collectingCountry box="[1113,1189,1590,1614]" name="Oman" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Omani</collectingCountry>
waters (
<bibRefCitation author="Henderson" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refString="Henderson, A. C., McIlwain, J. L., Al-Oufi, H. S. &amp; Al-Sheili, S. (2007) The Sultanate of Oman shark fishery: Species composition, seasonality and diversity. Fisheries Research, 86, 159 - 168." type="journal article" year="2007">
Henderson 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[186,244,1626,1650]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="2007.0">2007</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) and considered to be possibly present in the Gulf (
<bibRefCitation author="Compagno" box="[818,1071,1626,1651]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refString="Compagno, L., Dando, M., &amp; Fowler, S. (2005) A field guide to the sharks of the world. Harper Collins, London." type="book" year="2005">
Compagno 
<emphasis box="[949,998,1627,1651]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[1011,1071,1626,1650]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), although no records are known to the current authors; this species may be more likely to occur in the deeper waters of the northeastern Gulf.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1230,2011]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
Isolated records of the spadenose shark 
<taxonomicName authority="Muller &amp; Henle, 1838" authorityName="Muller &amp; Henle" authorityYear="1838" box="[660,1183,1698,1723]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Carcharhinidae" genus="Scoliodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carcharhiniformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="laticaudus">
<emphasis box="[660,898,1699,1723]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Scoliodon laticaudus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Muller" box="[916,1175,1698,1722]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refString="Muller, J. &amp; Henle, J. (1838 - 41) Systematische Beschreibung der Plagiostomen. Veit und Comp., Berlin." type="book" year="1838">
Müller &amp; Henle, 
<number box="[1118,1175,1698,1722]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="1838.0">1838</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
from fish community studies in 
<collectingCountry box="[264,346,1734,1758]" name="Kuwait" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Kuwait</collectingCountry>
Bay (
<bibRefCitation author="Wright" box="[413,622,1734,1759]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refString="Wright, J. M., Clayton, D. A. &amp; Bishop, J. M. (1990) Tidal movements of shallow water fishes in Kuwait Bay. Journal of Fish Biology, 37, 959 - 974." type="journal article" year="1990">
Wright 
<emphasis box="[500,549,1735,1759]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[564,622,1734,1758]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="1990.0">1990</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName box="[664,830,1735,1759]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Carcharhinidae" genus="Scoliodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carcharhiniformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="laticaudatus">
<emphasis box="[664,830,1735,1759]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">S. laticaudatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Wright" box="[845,1050,1734,1759]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refString="Wright, J. M., Abou-Seedo, F. &amp; Clayton, D. A. (1996) Long term changes in the fish assemblage of Sulaibikhat Bay, Kuwait. Kuwait Journal of Science and Engineering, 23, 47 - 60." type="journal article" year="1996">
Wright 
<emphasis box="[930,978,1734,1759]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[993,1050,1734,1758]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="1996.0">1996</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) require confirmation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1230,2011]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
The circumglobal sandbar shark 
<taxonomicName authority="Nardo, 1827" authorityName="Nardo" authorityYear="1827" box="[573,1011,1770,1795]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Carcharhinidae" genus="Carcharhinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carcharhiniformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="plumbeus">
<emphasis box="[573,843,1771,1795]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Carcharhinus plumbeus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Nardo" box="[859,1003,1770,1794]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refString="Nardo, G. D. (1827) Prodromus observationum et disquisitionum Adriaticae ichthyologiae. Giornale di fisica, chimica e storia naturale, medicina, ed arti, Dec. II, 10, 22 - 40." type="journal article" year="1827">
Nardo, 
<number box="[946,1003,1770,1794]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="1827.0">1827</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
has been reported (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Goubanov" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refString="Goubanov, E. P. &amp; Shleib, N. A. (1980). Sharks of the Arabian Gulf. Ministry of Public Works, Agricultural Department, Fisheries Divisions, Kuwait." type="book" year="1980">
Goubanov &amp; Shleib, 
<number box="[236,295,1806,1830]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="1980.0">1980</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Herdson" box="[307,469,1806,1830]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refString="Herdson, D. M. (1981) Elasmobranchs of the Arabian Gulf. Appendix 2 (p. 165 to 181) to The demersal fish resources of the south west Arabian Gulf. A Report on the British Ministry of Overseas Development and State of Bahrain Joint Research Project, 1974 to 1978. Unpublished report to the Ministry of Overseas Development." type="journal article" year="1981">
Herdson 
<number box="[410,469,1806,1830]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="1981.0">1981</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Krupp" box="[480,741,1806,1830]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refString="Krupp, F. &amp; Almarri, M. (1996) Fishes and fish assemblages of the Jubail Marine Wildlife Sanctuary. In: Krupp, F., Abuzinada, A. H., Nader, I. A. (Eds) A Marine Wildlife Sanctuary for the Arabian Gulf. Environmental Research and Conservation Following the 1991 Gulf War Oil Spill. NCWCD, Riyadh and Senckenberg Research Institute, Frankfurt a. M." type="journal volume" year="1996">
Krupp &amp; Almarri 
<number box="[684,741,1806,1830]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="1996.0">1996</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) and photographs of a specimen seen by the authors are more than likely to have originated from the Gulf, although unequivocal evidence is required.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1230,2011]" lastBlockId="12.[151,1436,151,284]" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="13" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<bibRefCitation author="Compagno" box="[199,417,1878,1902]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refString="Compagno, L. J. V. (1984 b) Carcharhinidae. In: Fischer, W. &amp; Bianchi, G. (Eds.) FAO species identification sheets for fishery purposes: Western Indian Ocean (Area 51). Volume V, Bony fishes, chimaeras, sharks, lobsters, shrimps and prawns, sea turtles. FAO, Rome." type="journal volume" year="1984" yearSuffix="b">
Compagno (
<number box="[336,394,1878,1902]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="1984.0">1984</number>
b)
</bibRefCitation>
raised the possibility that the critically endangered Ganges shark 
<taxonomicName authority="Muller &amp; Henle, 1839" authorityName="Muller &amp; Henle" authorityYear="1839" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Carcharhinidae" genus="Glyphis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carcharhiniformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gangeticus">
<emphasis box="[1149,1364,1878,1902]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Glyphis gangeticus</emphasis>
(Müller &amp; Henle, 
<number box="[297,354,1914,1938]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="1839.0">1839</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
may occur in the Gulf, and although this author did not pursue the idea (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Compagno" box="[1230,1432,1914,1938]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refString="Compagno, L. J. V. (1984 a) FAO Species Catalogue. Sharks of the World. An annotated and illustrated catalogue of shark species known to date. Part 2. Carcharhiniformes. FAO Fisheries Synopsis (125), Volume 4, Part 2. FAO, Rome." type="journal volume" year="1984" yearSuffix="a">
Compagno 
<number box="[1360,1419,1914,1938]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="1984.0">1984</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Compagno" box="[151,405,1950,1975]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refString="Compagno, L., Dando, M., &amp; Fowler, S. (2005) A field guide to the sharks of the world. Harper Collins, London." type="book" year="2005">
Compagno 
<emphasis box="[282,332,1950,1975]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[347,405,1950,1974]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) it was considered to be plausible given environmental changes over recent geological history (Moore 
<number box="[297,357,1986,2010]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="2011.0">2011</number>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Mahdi" box="[376,532,1986,2010]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refString="Mahdi, N. (1962) Fishes of Iraq. Ministry of Education, Baghdad." type="book" year="1962">
Mahdi (
<number box="[466,524,1986,2010]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="1962.0">1962</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
noted two separate species of freshwater shark occurring in the Tigris River as far upstream as Baghdad, although these may simply represent misidentification of 
<emphasis box="[1128,1244,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<taxonomicName box="[1128,1240,152,176]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Carcharhinidae" genus="Carcharhinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carcharhiniformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="leucas">C. leucas</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Nonetheless the undersampled (and highly threatened) Tigris-Euphrates-Karun system remains intriguing.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,151,284]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Randall (
<number box="[303,361,223,247]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1996.0">1996</number>
) noted that the whitetip reef shark 
<taxonomicName authority="Ruppell, 1837" authorityName="Ruppell" authorityYear="1837" box="[770,1174,223,248]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Carcharhinidae" genus="Triaenodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carcharhiniformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="obesus">
<emphasis box="[770,985,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Triaenodon obesus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ruppell" box="[1002,1167,223,247]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refString="Ruppell, W. P. E. S. (1837) Neue Wirbelthiere zu der Fauna von Abyssinien gehorig. Fische des Rothen Meeres. Frankfurt-am- Main." type="book" year="1837">
Rüppell, 
<number box="[1109,1167,223,247]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1837.0">1837</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
has not been recorded from the Gulf and our data support this.
</paragraph>
